# NoomiBodi Project Context

AI-powered nutrition tracking app built with React Native (TypeScript), Supabase backend, and Claude API.

## Architecture

### Screens (src/screens/)
- **QuickLogPage** ā€” daily calories/macros, add meal photo, weight log, weekly weight chart, smart suggestions, today's meals. Registered directly as the "Home" page in the flat pager.
- **ChatScreen** ā€” conversational interface with Claude, quick action chips, markdown rendering. Pushable RootStack screen accessed via TopBar chat bubble icon; includes themed back button when standalone.
- **MealsScreen** ā€” saved meals library with search, sort, macro filters, AI meal builder, share-with-friend via long-press. Registered as "MyMeals" page in the flat pager.
- **SharedMealsPage** ā€” "Share a Meal" button (meal picker ā†’ friend picker flow), received meals inbox with add-to-library, collapsible "Shared by You" section showing sent meals, unread indicators. Registered as "SharedMeals" page; reports unread count to MainTabs for SubTabBar badge.
- **ReportsScreen** ā€” calorie/weight charts with CustomBarChart, goal lines, interactive tooltips. Registered as "Reports" page.
- **InsightsPage** ā€” AI-generated insights. Registered as "Insights" page.
- **SocialScreen** ā€” activity feed, pending friend requests (collapsible), sent requests (collapsible), friends list (horizontal scroll), weekly leaderboard; "Add Friend" opens AddFriendModal
- **AddFriendModal** ā€” BottomSheet with user search, friendship status buttons (Follow/Pending/Accept/Friends)
- **FriendProfileScreen** ā€” RootStack screen showing friend's profile, stats card (streak, days tracked, adherence), plan summary, weight progress, average daily macros (all via `get_friend_stats` RPC); remove friend action; hidden if profile is private
- **ProfilePage** ā€” pushable RootStack screen (via TopBar profile picture). User profile picture, username, bio, stats, goals summary, "Edit Profile" button. Header has back arrow (left) and gear icon (right, navigates to SettingsScreen).
- **SettingsPage** ā€” pushable RootStack screen (via ProfilePage gear icon). Privacy toggle, API key, appearance, sign out, reset profile. Includes themed back button when standalone.
- **EditProfileScreen** ā€” RootStack screen for editing username, display name, bio, profile picture upload
- **AdminDashboard** ā€” admin-only page in the flat pager (conditionally shown)
- **OnboardingScreen** ā€” multi-step onboarding (API key, profile info, goals, activity, account, username, details, Claude plan); styles in separate `OnboardingScreen.styles.tsx` using `createStyles(colors, isDark)` pattern
- **SignInScreen** ā€” standalone sign-in screen shown after sign-out (without profile reset); supports email/password, Apple, and Google sign-in
- **EmailVerificationScreen** ā€” blocks entry to main app until email is verified; polls session every 5s, has resend with 60s cooldown; skipped for social sign-ins (Google/Apple)

### Services (src/services/)
- **claude.ts** ā€” Anthropic Messages API integration, system prompts, response parsing, AI usage logging
- **claudeTools.ts** ā€” RAG tool definitions + execution for Claude function calling
- **mealLog.ts** ā€” daily_logs CRUD (Supabase + offline queue); triggers streak milestone check after successful log
- **savedMeals.ts** ā€” saved_meals CRUD + `clearAllSavedMeals()` for profile reset
- **storage.ts** ā€” AsyncStorage (API key, messages) + Supabase profiles/plans; `UserProfile` includes social fields (username, displayName, profilePictureUrl, bio, isPrivate); `clearUserProfile()` clears profiles, user_plans, daily_logs, weight_logs, user_insights
- **profileService.ts** ā€” username validation, availability check, user search via `public_profiles` view (ILIKE on username/display_name), admin search via `profiles` (includes email/role), profile picture upload to Supabase Storage, partial profile field updates, `suggestUsernameFromEmail()`
- **friendships.ts** ā€” friend request CRUD (send/accept/decline/remove); accept/decline restricted to recipient via `following_id` filter; queries for accepted friends, pending received/sent, friendship status check between two users
- **activityFeed.ts** ā€” streak milestone insertion, duplicate checking, friend activity feed query (RLS handles privacy); `checkAndRecordMilestone()` for auto-logging milestones
- **leaderboard.ts** ā€” weekly leaderboard calculation (adherence % = days hit calorie goal / 7); filters out private users; returns ranked list
- **sharedMeals.ts** ā€” share meals with friends, inbox query (two-step: shared_meals + saved_meals/public_profiles), sent shares query, unread count, mark as read (recipient-only), delete (recipient-only), copy to saved meals
- **reportData.ts** ā€” weight logs (upserts same-day entries), daily summaries, overview stats; `getFriendStats(friendId)` calls `get_friend_stats` RPC for friend profile data
- **adminAnalytics.ts** ā€” admin dashboard data queries
- **analytics.ts** ā€” weight prediction, adherence patterns, correlations
- **insightGenerator.ts** ā€” AI-generated insights via Claude
- **offlineStore.ts** ā€” offline queue + read cache + `clearOfflineData()` for profile reset
- **supabase.ts** ā€” Supabase client initialization
- **notifications.ts** ā€” FCM token registration/unregistration, `sendNotification()` (invokes Edge Function), `sendMilestoneNotifications()`, `claim_device_token` RPC call for stale token cleanup
- **widgetBridge.ts** ā€” native bridge to write widget data to App Group UserDefaults and reload WidgetKit timelines via `SharedGroupPreferences`
- **widgetDataSync.ts** ā€” aggregates today's calories/macros from `daily_logs` and goals from `user_plans`, then calls `updateWidgetData()` to push to the widget

### iOS Widgets (ios/NoomiBodi Widget/)
Native WidgetKit extension written in Swift. Shares data with the main app via App Group `group.noomibodi` using `UserDefaults(suiteName:)` with key `widgetData` (JSON string).

**Widget types:**
- **Home screen small** (`systemSmall`) ā€” calorie ring + consumed/goal text
- **Home screen medium** (`systemMedium`) ā€” calorie ring + protein/carbs/fat rows + camera button (bottom-right, deep links to `noomibodi://add-photo` ā†’ launches camera for meal logging)
- **Lock screen circular** (`accessoryCircular`) ā€” calorie ring with remaining calories
- **Lock screen rectangular** (`accessoryRectangular`) ā€” calories + protein/carbs/fat gauges
- **Control Center** ā€” timer toggle (placeholder, not wired to nutrition data)
- **Live Activity** ā€” Dynamic Island placeholder (not yet integrated)

**Data flow:** Meal logged ā†’ Supabase `daily_logs` ā†’ `syncWidgetData()` fetches today's totals + goals ā†’ `updateWidgetData()` writes JSON to App Group UserDefaults ā†’ `reloadWidgets()` triggers `WidgetCenter.shared.reloadAllTimelines()` ā†’ widget reads `widgetData` and refreshes.

**Sync call sites:** QuickLogPage (after meal log, weight log, offline sync), ChatScreen (after send/AI response), MealsScreen (after save), SmartRecommendations (after suggested meal log), offlineStore (after offline sync).

**Native bridge files:** `ios/SharedGroupPreferences.h` + `.m` (Obj-C React Native module exposing `set(suiteName, key, value)` and `reloadWidgets()`).

### Push Notifications (Firebase + Supabase Edge Function)
iOS push notifications via Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) ā†’ APNs.

**Notification types:**
- `friend_request` ā€” when a user sends a friend request
- `friend_accepted` ā€” when a recipient accepts a friend request
- `shared_meal` ā€” when a friend shares a meal
- `streak_milestone` ā€” when a friend hits a streak milestone (sent to all non-private accepted friends)

**Architecture:**
- **Client:** `@react-native-firebase/messaging` (modular API) for token management and message listeners
- **Server:** Supabase Edge Function `send-notification` (Deno) ā€” validates caller JWT, looks up recipient FCM tokens from `device_tokens`, dispatches via FCM HTTP v1 API with Google service account JWT
- **Native:** `AppDelegate.swift` configures Firebase, implements `UNUserNotificationCenterDelegate` for foreground banners, clears badge on `applicationDidBecomeActive`

**Token lifecycle:** Register on app launch ā†’ upsert to `device_tokens` ā†’ refresh via `onTokenRefresh` listener ā†’ delete on sign-out ā†’ stale tokens cleaned via `claim_device_token()` RPC

**Call sites for `sendNotification()`:** AddFriendModal (friend_request, friend_accepted), SocialScreen (friend_accepted), SharedMealsPage (shared_meal), MealsScreen (shared_meal), mealLog.ts (streak_milestone via `sendMilestoneNotifications`)

**Edge Function secrets (Supabase Dashboard ā†’ Edge Functions ā†’ Secrets):** `FCM_PROJECT_ID`, `FCM_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON` (Firebase service account JSON), plus auto-injected `SUPABASE_URL`, `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`

**Deployment:** `supabase functions deploy send-notification --no-verify-jwt` (gateway JWT verification disabled; function validates JWT internally)

### Branding & Assets (src/assets/)
- **Noomi** ā€” the app's mascot, a purple phoenix. The primary Noomi image is `src/assets/noomi.png` (1024px, transparent background).
- **App icons**: Noomi-based icons installed for iOS (`Images.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset/`), iOS widget (`NoomiBodi Widget/Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset/`), and Android (`mipmap-*/ic_launcher.png` + `ic_launcher_round.png`).
- **Chat avatar**: Assistant messages in ChatScreen show a circular Noomi avatar (22x22) next to the "Noomi" label. The chat empty state uses a larger (80x80) Noomi image with "Chat with Noomi" title.
- **Color palette** derived from Noomi: accent purple `#7C3AED`, lighter purple `#8B5CF6`, deep purple `#5B21B6`, light purple bg `#EDE9FE` / dark purple bg `#1a1033`. The old green accent (`#4CAF50`) has been fully replaced.

### Key Patterns
- **Theming**: `useTheme()` hook from `ThemeContext` ā€” apply colors via inline styles `{ color: colors.text }`, not in StyleSheet.create. For screens with separate style files (OnboardingScreen), use `createStyles(colors, isDark)` function pattern with `useMemo`.
- **Auth**: `useAuth()` from `AuthContext` ā€” wraps Supabase auth; provides `signIn`, `signUp`, `signInWithApple`, `signInWithGoogle`, `signOut`, `resetPassword`, `resendVerificationEmail`, `refreshSession`
- **Social Auth**: Apple Sign-In via `@invertase/react-native-apple-authentication` (library auto-hashes nonce with SHA256 before sending to Apple, so pass RAW nonce to both the library and Supabase); Google Sign-In via `@react-native-google-signin/google-signin` (patched native iOS code via `patch-package` to support nonce parameter; Google does NOT auto-hash, so pass SHA256 hashed nonce to Google + raw nonce to Supabase `signInWithIdToken`)
- **Identity Linking**: Supabase automatic linking is enabled by default ā€” same email across Google, Apple, and email/password maps to one account
- **Email Verification**: After email/password sign-up, user completes onboarding but is blocked from the main app by `EmailVerificationScreen` until `email_confirmed_at` is set; social sign-ins skip this
- **App Navigation States**: `App.tsx` manages screen state as `'loading' | 'onboarding' | 'signIn' | 'emailVerification' | 'main'`; sign-out goes to `signIn`, profile reset goes to `onboarding`; `RootStack` includes `EditProfileScreen`, `FriendProfileScreen`, `ProfileScreen`, `SettingsScreen`, and `ChatScreen` as pushable screens on top of `MainTabs`
- **Flat Pager Navigation**: `MainTabs` uses `createMaterialTopTabNavigator` as a flat swipeable pager with all screens registered individually: Home, MyMeals, SharedMeals, Reports, Insights, Social (, Admin). A persistent `TopBar` (profile picture left ā†’ ProfileScreen, chat bubble right ā†’ ChatScreen) sits above the pager. A `SubTabBar` (icon-based segmented control) appears for multi-page tab groups (Meals, Reports). A `CustomBottomTabBar` groups pages into tab groups (Home, Meals, Reports, Social, Admin) and highlights the active group. Navigation between tabs via swipe or bottom tab press; sub-page switching via SubTabBar or swipe.
- **Deep Links**: `useDeepLink` hook in QuickLogPage handles `noomibodi://quick-log` and `noomibodi://add-photo` (both launch camera). Widget uses `add-photo` for camera button, `quick-log` as default tap URL.
- **Social Features**: Bidirectional friendships (both must accept), privacy toggle (hides activity/leaderboard), streak milestones auto-logged on meal log, weekly leaderboard (Mon-Sun adherence %), meal sharing between accepted friends
- **Impersonation**: `ImpersonationContext` ā€” admin-only session switching for testing other accounts; `ImpersonationBanner` red border when active; `ImpersonateModal` for admin dashboard search
- **Modals**: use `BottomSheet` component for consistent drag-to-dismiss, dark backdrop (AddFriendModal, FriendPickerModal, MealPickerModal, ImpersonateModal use this pattern)
- **Reusable components**: `ChatInputBox` (chat input with image attachment), `ThemedMarkdown` (themed markdown renderer used in chat, AI meal builder, quick log descriptions), `MealPickerModal` (select a meal from library for sharing), `FriendPickerModal` (select friends for sharing), `TopBar` (persistent top bar with profile picture + chat bubble), `SubTabBar` (icon-based segmented control for sub-pages), `CustomBottomTabBar` (grouped tab bar for flat pager), `CustomBarChart` (interactive bar chart with tooltips, goal lines, label thinning)
- **Loading & Error Components**: `LoadingScreen` (full-screen spinner), `SkeletonLoader` (animated placeholder shapes: `SkeletonText`, `SkeletonCircle`, `SkeletonCard`, `SkeletonRow`), `ErrorState` (error message + retry button, supports `compact` mode), `EmptyState` (icon + title + subtitle + optional CTA, supports `compact` mode), `LoadingButton` (async-aware button with auto-spinner and error Alert), `OfflineBanner` (animated slide-in/out with "Back online" message), `ErrorBoundary` (app-level crash recovery)
- **Error Handling**: `getUserFriendlyError(err)` in `src/utils/errorMessages.ts` maps technical errors (Supabase, HTTP, Claude, auth, network) to user-facing messages. `isNetworkError(err)` is also exported from there (single source of truth). All screens use these for Alert and ErrorState messages.
- **Retry Logic**: `withRetry(fn, options?)` in `src/utils/retry.ts` ā€” exponential backoff for transient failures (429, 5xx, rate limit). Applied to `claude.ts` and `notifications.ts`.
- **Data Fetching**: `useAsyncData(fetcher, options?)` hook standardizes loading/error/refresh pattern. Screens distinguish `loading` (first load, shows skeleton) from `refreshing` (subsequent load, shows RefreshControl spinner).
- **Stale-Time Guard**: `useStaleFetch(fetchFn, staleTimeMs)` hook prevents redundant re-fetching on tab switches. Returns `fetchIfStale` (skip if fresh), `forceFetch` (pull-to-refresh), `markStale` (invalidate after mutations). Applied to all data-loading screens with per-screen stale times (15sā€“60s).
- **Optimistic Updates**: UI updates immediately for reversible operations (friend accept/decline, meal delete, shared meal delete) with rollback on failure.
- **Profanity filter**: `src/utils/profanityFilter.ts` ā€” client-side check for usernames/display names/bios; skipped for admin accounts
- **Push Notifications**: `useNotifications` hook in `App.tsx` ā€” registers FCM token, listens for foreground/background messages, navigates on tap; `notifications.ts` service handles token CRUD and Edge Function invocation
- **Offline**: writes queued locally via `offlineStore.ts`, synced on reconnect via `useOfflineSync` hook
- **Day change**: `useDayChange` hook triggers refresh at midnight

## Conventions

- TypeScript strict, functional components only
- Styles via `StyleSheet.create` at bottom of file; theme colors applied inline in JSX
- For screens with separate style files, use `createStyles(colors: ThemeColors, isDark: boolean)` function that returns `StyleSheet.create({...})`, consumed via `useMemo` in the component
- `colors.surface` for card backgrounds, `colors.border` for card borders, `borderRadius: 14` for cards
- 12px spacing between sibling components on QuickLogPage
- All modals use `BottomSheet` wrapper (tap/drag dismiss, dark backdrop)
- Every screen with async data uses skeleton loaders (not ActivityIndicator) for initial load, `RefreshControl` for pull-to-refresh, `ErrorState` for fetch failures, and `EmptyState` for zero-data scenarios
- All error messages shown to users go through `getUserFriendlyError()` ā€” never show raw error messages
- Tab-switching uses `useStaleFetch` to avoid redundant re-fetches; data stays visible while background refresh runs
- Claude responses parsed with markers: `[MEAL_DATA]`, `[PLAN_START]`, `[SAVE_MEAL]`, `[PORTION]`
- AI usage logged to `ai_usage_logs` table after every Claude API call
- Onboarding and auth screens always follow system theme (ThemeProvider defaults to `mode: 'system'`)
- Primary buttons invert in dark mode: white bg with dark text (light mode: dark bg with white text)
- Apple Sign-In button inverts in dark mode (white bg/dark text); Google button stays blue in both themes
- Accent color is purple `#7C3AED` (Noomi's palette) ā€” use `colors.accent` from theme; never use green `#4CAF50`
- New accent-colored UI backgrounds use `#EDE9FE` (light) / `#1a1033` (dark); accent text uses `#5B21B6` (light) / `#A78BFA` (dark)
- Noomi avatar (`require('../assets/noomi.png')`) should appear wherever the AI persona is represented (chat messages, empty states)
- iOS widget accent color matches the app (`0x7C3AED` in `NoomiBodi_Widget.swift`)

## Database (Supabase + RLS)
Tables: `profiles`, `user_plans`, `saved_meals`, `daily_logs`, `weight_logs`, `user_insights`, `ai_usage_logs`, `friendships`, `activity_feed`, `shared_meals`, `device_tokens`
Roles in `profiles.role`: `admin`, `beta`, `pro`, `standard`, `byok` (default)

**Social columns on `profiles`:** `username` (UNIQUE), `display_name`, `profile_picture_url`, `bio`, `is_private` (default false)

**Views:**
- `public_profiles` ā€” security definer view exposing only safe columns (`id`, `username`, `display_name`, `profile_picture_url`, `bio`, `is_private`, `created_at`). All social cross-user lookups use this view. Excludes `email`, `gender`, `age`, `height_cm`, `current_weight_kg`, `activity_level`, `role`. GRANT to `authenticated`, REVOKE from `anon`/`public`.

**Social tables:**
- `friendships` ā€” bidirectional friend system (follower_id, following_id, status: pending/accepted/declined). Both users can view/delete; only follower can create; only recipient (`following_id`) can accept/decline (UPDATE).
- `activity_feed` ā€” user achievements (streak milestones). RLS enforces privacy: friends' activity visible only if friendship accepted AND `is_private = false`.
- `shared_meals` ā€” share saved meals between friends (meal_id FK ā†’ saved_meals). Sender must own the meal; recipient can mark read/delete. `saved_meals` has an RLS policy allowing recipients to view shared meals.

**Push notification tables:**
- `device_tokens` ā€” FCM token storage (user_id, fcm_token, platform). RLS: users manage own tokens. UNIQUE(user_id, fcm_token). ON DELETE CASCADE from auth.users.

**Helper functions:**
- `is_admin()` ā€” SECURITY DEFINER function checking `profiles.role = 'admin'`, used in admin RLS policies to avoid recursion.
- `claim_device_token(p_fcm_token)` ā€” SECURITY DEFINER function that deletes stale `device_tokens` entries for the same FCM token belonging to a different user. Called during token registration to handle device reuse across accounts.
- `get_friend_stats(p_friend_id)` ā€” SECURITY DEFINER function returning JSONB with friend's stats (streak, adherence), plan, weight progress, and avg macros. Checks accepted friendship and non-private profile. Called by `FriendProfileScreen` via `reportData.getFriendStats()`.

**Storage bucket:** `profile-pictures` (public). Folder structure: `{user_id}/{timestamp}.jpg`. URLs stored in `profiles.profile_picture_url`.

See `docs/database_schema.md` for full schema, `docs/roles.md` for role details.

